com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class CanUnmergeRecordsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.CanUnmergeRecordsRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SiperianObjectUidProvider, SystemProvider, Serializable

    public class CanUnmergeRecordsRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
implements SystemProvider
    Represents a request object to determine whether the specified cross-reference record (XREF) can be unmerged from the consolidated base object record.

    To add cross-reference records to a base object record, you can consolidate two base object records or use the ROWID_OBJECT of a base object record to directly add the cross-reference records. When you add a cross-reference record by using the ROWID_OBJECT of a base object that does not have the PKEY_SOURCE_OBJECT value set and if the base object does not have a cross-reference record for the specified system, a new cross-reference record is added with 'edit' status.

    You can unmerge a cross-reference record only if at least two cross-reference records of the base object are not edit cross-reference records. You cannot unmerge a cross-reference record if it is not an edit cross-reference record and all other cross-reference records of the base object are edit cross-reference records.

    Note: When you use the Audit Manager in the Hub Console, use CanUnmergeRecordsRequest in any specific system. After you enable auditing for a request, the MDM Hub logs the request invocation and response in the audit log. For more information about auditing, see the Informatica Multidomain MDM Configuration Guide.

    Use Case
    In an application that has a custom UI for data stewards, you can create a button that uses CanUnmergeRecordsRequest to identify whether the cross-reference record can be unmerged.

    Usage Example
    The following example determines whether the cross-reference record with the PKEY_SOURCE_OBJECT key 782 and system 'SALES' can be unmerged from the base object record.

    CanUnmergeRecordsRequest request = new CanUnmergeRecordsRequest();
    XrefKey xrefKey = new XrefKey();
    recordKey.setSourceKey("782");
    recordKey.setSystemName("SALES");
    request.setXrefKey(recordKey);
    request.setSiperianObjectUid("PACKAGE.CUSTOMER_UPDATE");
    CanUnmergeRecordsResponse response = (CanUnmergeRecordsResponse) sipClient.process(request);
